&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Medicine team, as a Strategic and Operational Delivery Improvement Manager, substantively, supporting both Sub Group A and Subgroup B to transact and realise key tactical delivery objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is pivotal to ensuring the realisation of clinical pathway improvement and new models of delivery, mainly internally but also working with identified partners where opportunities for integrated working allows. There is an expectation that this individual has relevant experience in project or management and clinical pathways service improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants will be automatically invited to Interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion, please liaise with Sue Chamberlain who will enable you to speak with Harpal Randeva, Asad Ali, Beth Harrison, John Elliot, Natalie Bell or Jan Jayatilake.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will close once suitable applications are received.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSue ChamberlainJob titleInterim PA to Medicine GroupEmail addresssusan.chamberlain@uhcw.nhs.ukTelephone number02476 967628&lt;/p&gt;
